      <description>&lt;figure&gt;&#xA;    &lt;picture class=&#34;main-image&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &#xA;&#xA;&#xA;            &#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;            &#xA;            &#xA;    &lt;/picture&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;figcaption&gt;&lt;/figcaption&gt;&#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;OK, so you&amp;rsquo;ve read my &#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#x9;&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;https://lrg.io/technology-and-our-future/why-are-you-still-on-x/&#34; &#xA; &#xA;target=&#34;&#34;&#xA;class=&#34;relative&#34; &#xA;data-domain=&#34;&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;link-text&#34;&gt;plea to leave X&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;hostname-text&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; , and you&amp;rsquo;re thinking&amp;hellip; ok, they have a point, but&amp;hellip;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;how-do-we-start&#34;&gt;How do we start?&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;First of all, I have to acknowledge that this isn&amp;rsquo;t a simple as just deleting your account. Many organisations have had a presence on X (fka Twitter) for a long time and have built up a substantial audience. I&amp;rsquo;m not suggesting you throw that away, yet.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
